[14] Hong Kong
Date: Tue 9 Apr 2019, 1:39 PM
Source: Ejinsight [abridged, edited]
http://www.ejinsight.com/20190409-five-more-measles-cases-including-pregnant-woman-confirmed/


Five more people, including a 28-year-old pregnant woman, were confirmed to have contracted measles in Hong Kong, taking the number of cases this year [2019] to 61, the Centre for Health Protection (CHP) under the Department of Health said.

The 28-year-old patient is the 1st pregnant woman to have been infected by the measles virus this year [2019], the CHP said. As many as 28, or nearly half of the cases, were associated with the measles outbreak at the Hong Kong International Airport. All of the 5 new cases were in stable condition, the Hong Kong Economic Journal reported.

The pregnant woman had a good health record prior to contracting measles and no travel history during the incubation or communicable period. She attended the Accident and Emergency Department of Pok Oi Hospital on [5 Apr 2019] and was transferred to Tuen Mun Hospital for admission and treatment on the same day. She had received 2 doses of measles vaccination in the past.

Investigation also revealed that the pregnant patient had received regular antenatal check-ups at the Madam Yung Fung Shee Maternal and Child Health Center in Yuen Long during the communicable period.

The health department has stepped up infection control measures in the center and reminded staff members and visitors to take proper infection control measures like wearing masks and washing hands. Relevant epidemiological investigations and contact tracing are also continuing.

Dr. Kun Ka-yan, a specialist in obstetrics and gynecology, pointed out that it is most dangerous for a pregnant woman who contracts measles 2 or 3 weeks before delivery as she would not have enough time to develop sufficient antibodies to protect her baby.

As such, the baby might end up being infected by the measles virus and born with some serious complications, such as encephalitis, which could impede the baby's future physical and mental development or even prove life-threatening, Kun said. The chances of miscarriage will increase if the infection happens before 12 weeks. If the infection happens after 12 weeks of pregnancy, the chance of a premature birth will go up, Kun said.

Three of the 5 new cases worked at the airport, including a 25-year-old woman and 2 men aged 23 and 29, all of whom had received 2 doses of measles vaccination in the past. The 5th case involved a 41-year-old man with good past health. His measles vaccination history was unknown but he had traveled to the Philippines during the incubation and communicable period.

The Central Committee on Infectious Disease and Emergency Responses of the Hospital Authority (HA), along with CHP representatives, held a meeting on [Mon 8 Apr 2019] to discuss the latest situation of measles infection.

After the meeting, the HA said the current staff measles vaccination program will cover staff members of Accident and Emergency Departments as well as General Out-patient Clinic triage stations from [Wed 10 Apr 2019].

According to Dr. Vivien Chuang Wai-man, HA chief manager for infection, emergency and contingency, infectious disease experts agreed at the meeting that vaccinating these healthcare workers would help reduce their risk of infection and further infecting other patients seeking consultation. The 1st phase of healthcare staff measles vaccination program began last week, with more than 1300 staff members working in high-risk departments and with inadequate immunity having been vaccinated as of [Mon 8 Apr 2019] night.

