[15] Philippines: Sitrep 9
Date: Sun 14 Apr 2019
Source: Reliefweb, a World Health Organization, UN Children's Fund report [abridged, edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/philippines/unicef-who-philippines-measles-outbreak-situation-report-9-14-april-2019


UNICEF-WHO Philippines: Measles Outbreak, Situation Report 9, 14 April 2019
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Overview
Current measles outbreak started late 2017 in Mindanao. In 2018, 20 827 cases were reported with 199 deaths. Outbreak and supplementary immunization activities in 2018 were ineffective in addressing the outbreak as the immunization activity was met with increased vaccine hesitancy due to the Dengue vaccine controversy. Weak routine immunization leading to a decrease in overall immunization coverage in recent years resulted in significant immunity gaps among younger children.

The Philippines Department of Health (DoH) declared measles outbreaks in 5 Regions (Region NCR, III, IV-A, VI, VII) on [7 Feb 2019], whereas cases are being reported from all 17 Regions. DoH issued guidelines for nation-wide measles vaccination accompanied by Oral Polio Vaccine (OPV) and Vitamin A distribution until end of March [2019], prioritizing unvaccinated children between 6 and 59 months; schoolchildren from kindergarten to grade 6; and adults who voluntarily wish to be vaccinated against measles.

Current Situation
Between [1 Jan and 5 Apr 2019], 28 362 measles cases including 389 deaths were officially reported through the routine surveillance system from the DOH, with a Case Fatality rate of 1.37% (see Table 1).

With a median age of 3 years old, 53% of measles cases are under 5 years of age. A total of 53% of measles cases are male.

With a median age of 1 year old, 84% of all deaths are children under the age of 5, and 61% of measles deaths are male. Most deaths are reported from Region III, IV-A, VIII and NCR.

As of 5 Apr 2019, 90% of cases have no documented vaccination status. DoH data shows that 3% of cases had been previously vaccinated with 2 doses of measles vaccine. The vaccination status of the remainder of cases is unknown.

