[16] Australia and New Zealand
Date: Thu 11 Apr 2019
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
https://protect2.fireeye.com/url?k=4f742b84-1350dde5-4f76d2b1-0cc47a6d17e0-e4127049d6fc1f89&u=http://outbreaknewstoday.com/measles-new-zealand-australia-updates-79206/


New Zealand
-----------
In New Zealand, health officials have confirmed 72 measles cases since the beginning of the year [2019], including 23 that required hospitalization.

More than half the cases were reported from Canterbury, while nearly 2 out of 10 cases were from Waikato.

The majority of cases have occurred in children, adolescents and young adults aged under 29 years.

Australia
---------
Australian officials have reported 83 measles cases through [5 Apr 2019]. This is compared to 103 and 81 cases in all of 2018 and 2017, respectively.

Nationally, vaccination rates (receiving 2 doses of the vaccine) for children under 2 years of age are below the 95% threshold (93.5%).

In addition, Health Minister Greg Hunt warned that due to changing vaccine schedules for Australians born between 1966 and 1994, some people may have received only 1 dose of vaccine, instead of 2, making them more susceptible to infection.

